# Portfolio And Cross-Customer Deck Display Names

For human-facing deck `name` values in portfolio or cross-customer decks:

- Use plain English words with standard capitalization.
- Do not use underscores (`_`) or dashes (`-`) in the display name.
- Do not start the display name with numbers or punctuation.
- Keep internal deck `id` values unchanged unless explicitly requested.

Examples:
- `Support Review Portfolio` (good)
- `Engineering Portfolio Review` (good)
- `support_review_portfolio` (bad)
- `00 - Portfolio Health Review` (bad)
- `Engineering-Portfolio` (bad)
